# [DMM](../wg/dmm.html)

## Summary

The Distributed Mobility Management (DMM) Working Group met at IETF 126 in Vienna. The session was chaired by Satoru Matsushima (co-chair Sri Gundavelli was unable to attend). The group discussed the status of active working group drafts, reviewed recent updates to MUP architecture, mobile traffic steering, and SRv6 mobile user plane drafts, and explored future mobile user plane evolution and requirements for 5G and 6G networks.

---

## Key Discussion Points

### Working Group Status & IESG Review
*   **Presenter:** Satoru Matsushima
*   **Slides:** [WG Status](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-dmm-wg-status-01)
*   **Discussion:** 
    *   The "TN-aware mobility" draft has an active Discuss position from the OPS Area AD (Tommy Jensen) regarding whether it is presented as the only solution for mobility slicing. 
